The paper discusses the de-anonymization of communications on anonymity systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of coding theory and information theory, which are covered in the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and analysis of network flows, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
